      "date": "2022-09-07 20:39:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> can you please provide more info that just \"it looks caused OOM\" ?\n\n > Passed enforced test custom-101 on CentOS 8.5/aarch64, CentOS\n > 8.5/x86_64 uploaded by Trevis Autotest from trevis-108vm5:\n > https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/7bd7b9d5-6ca0-497a-8a01-77218c4d25d9\n > ran 3 tests.\n\nIt looks like lnet-selftest on aarch64 passed with this patch reverted, when it is failing 100% since 2022-09-01 with it applied.  \n\nI'm happy to land a fix to the problem instead of reverting it, but this is now causing all patches to fail testing and be unable to land (retesting will not help if 100% failure), so a solution needs to be found quickly.",
